data.text: @very_stupid_man @JBHockeyThought But in comparison to Marvel I wouldn’t say TFA, Rogue One, TLJ, and Solo even come close to what Marvel’s been doing for the past 10 years. I think the only one I didn’t really care for is the second Thor, but even then 19-for-20 ain’t bad at all

@JBHockeyThought @very_stupid_man On the flip side, maybe it’s just time to take a step back and reevaluate things. Obviously they aren’t producing the same quality that Marvel is every year, and if they’re not going to do anything but lose money from here on they ought to just take their time to figure it out
@very_stupid_man Yeah, Solo was ok. An obi-wan movie would be awesome and I think that one’s next in line...hopefully

@very_stupid_man But I can’t say I think TLJ fixed much of anything, it’s tough to develop a solid story when the setup is rocky at best but sheesh, they really ought to just stick to the main story spinoffs at this point, because I thought Rogue One was great.

@very_stupid_man I agree that TFA wasn’t a good setup, it did some things right (like vaguely introducing snoke and bringing back old characters) but I hate how they’re slowly killing everybody off. People want to see the heroes be heroic, not just show up for fan service and get keel hauled

@very_stupid_man Honestly I would’ve liked the throne scene more if they would’ve established snoke. Like, he’s introduced as a supreme leader and then whoop, gone. Maybe nitpicky, but Rey also completely misses a cue and one of the Crayola guards swings up and over, it looks ridiculous
@ClubShildt8 I’ve found somebody I can trust for once ❤️
